<i>He told me "whomever amongst us who's
killed as a martyr should go to paradise</i>

01:35.563 --> 01:38.999
<i>to lead the luxurious life
that he's never seen."</i>

01:39.099 --> 01:41.769
<i>"God is great" he repeats.</i>

01:41.869 --> 01:44.371
<i>No one knows how long
the battle will continue,</i>

01:44.471 --> 01:47.900
<i>but in a country long ravaged
with poverty, anger and violence,</i>

01:48.000 --> 01:52.146
<i>one thing is certain, there will always be
those willing to pay the ultimate price,</i>

01:52.246 --> 01:54.826
<i>to make their voices heard.</i>

02:06.292 --> 02:08.701
Would you like a brochure?

02:09.294 --> 02:12.017
Hi, sir, would you like a brochure?

02:14.867 --> 02:16.470
Hi, sir.

02:16.570 --> 02:19.158
Would you like a brochure?

02:21.708 --> 02:24.044
Would you like a brochure?

02:24.144 --> 02:25.885
Sir?

02:35.121 --> 02:36.590
Okay, then.

02:36.690 --> 02:38.888
- Hi, ma'am, would you like a brochure?
- No thank you.

02:45.131 --> 02:49.803
So you've outlined the absent father,
bipolar mother, self harm issues,

02:49.903 --> 02:53.340
and history of previous suicide attempts.

02:53.734 --> 02:56.310
Yep, toxicology off the charts.

02:56.410 --> 02:58.712
Poor thing.

02:58.812 --> 03:01.983
And on the day...

03:02.783 --> 03:05.319
you were the person who signed her out
as being okay to leave.

03:05.419 --> 03:06.720
Yes, I did.

03:06.820 --> 03:09.837
- Which is... which is...
- Yeah, I...

03:14.827 --> 03:17.923
Travis, is there something that you...

03:21.050 --> 03:23.903
want to add to the file?

03:25.072 --> 03:29.714
About her condition or any of the symptoms
that she may have presented?

03:31.377 --> 03:33.257
Do you know what she asked me one time?

03:35.115 --> 03:37.552
She asked me...

03:38.252 --> 03:41.767
if I thought it was possible
to treat someone's soul.

03:43.756 --> 03:45.926
Do you think that...

03:46.026 --> 03:48.096
that we can treat someone's soul?

03:49.896 --> 03:52.948
I know. I know.

03:54.100 --> 03:57.872
It's just I look at these people
across the table and...

03:58.222 --> 04:01.998
and I can see that there's something
in there that I'm missing.

04:02.960 --> 04:05.429
And I don't know what the fuck it is.

04:05.529 --> 04:07.765
- Travis...
- We talked about her life, okay?

04:07.865 --> 04:10.788
Not her file because for once in my life
I wanted to help someone

04:10.888 --> 04:13.304
in this fucking place.

04:13.404 --> 04:15.745
Travis, look, it is tough,

04:15.845 --> 04:18.404
I get it. But this is our job.

04:19.043 --> 04:21.410
We treat sick people.

04:21.510 --> 04:24.815
And I know you must be feeling like there
was something you could've done but...

04:24.915 --> 04:27.291
No, you're wrong.

04:27.818 --> 04:30.285
I don't feel anything.

04:30.521 --> 04:32.971
I can't feel anything.

04:33.574 --> 04:35.537
But thank you.

04:44.834 --> 04:47.885
- Good morning, Trevor.
- Morning, Doctor Bell.

04:53.009 --> 04:55.383
So, Rachel...

04:55.612 --> 04:58.447
Hi, there. I'm Doctor Bell.

04:59.532 --> 05:01.302
How's your week been?

05:01.652 --> 05:04.188
- Good.
- Good.

05:04.488 --> 05:09.723
And the medication, you've been
on the new medication for...

05:10.360 --> 05:13.503
About a month now, do we need
to make any adjustments?

05:13.831 --> 05:16.456
No. I feel better.

05:16.556 --> 05:20.780
Better. And are you sleeping
uninterrupted through the night?

05:25.441 --> 05:28.312
And on a scale of one to ten,

05:28.412 --> 05:32.116
how would you rate
Tuesday night's lasagne?

05:33.316 --> 05:36.404
- A seven.
- Seven. Interesting.

05:36.504 --> 05:40.699
I would have gone with eight. I thought
they did something pretty special there.

05:50.032 --> 05:52.603
A few days ago
I was down south at a party.

05:52.703 --> 05:55.105
I'd had a few beers, a pill,

05:55.205 --> 05:58.797
- bit to smoke, but I was cool.
- Okay.

05:58.897 --> 06:01.578
So... so I go to the kitchen,
to find some ice, and...

06:01.678 --> 06:05.845
- You took ice as well?
- For my beverage, relax, dude.

06:06.750 --> 06:09.169
Okay. Sorry.

06:09.269 --> 06:12.956
I turn around, and God
and the devil are standing there.

06:13.056 --> 06:16.873
God goes out to the patio and the devil's
standing right there behind me.

06:16.973 --> 06:19.519
- With big horns.
- That's interesting.

06:19.619 --> 06:22.095
Yeah. And I said to the devil, mate...

06:22.195 --> 06:24.518
you have no love in your life,
that's the trouble with you.

06:25.168 --> 06:27.204
That's why you do what you do.

06:27.304 --> 06:31.241
Devil couldn't forgive himself.
That's the message, man. Bring love.

06:31.341 --> 06:34.925
Wait. What did the devil
have to forgive himself for?

06:35.245 --> 06:39.216
- Have to ask him yourself, mate.
- No, Dean, seriously.

06:39.316 --> 06:43.258
What do you think that the devil
had to forgive himself for?

07:28.563 --> 07:30.000
Hello?

07:30.100 --> 07:33.270
<i>Hi. I just... I was
in the city and I just...</i>

07:33.370 --> 07:37.284
- Who is this?
- <i>I'm sorry, it's Rachel.</i>

07:37.384 --> 07:38.411
Rachel?

07:39.610 --> 07:43.387
- <i>We met at the hospital, the other day...</i>
- How did you get this number?

07:43.487 --> 07:46.360
<i>I was just in the city and I...
I was walking around and...</i>

07:46.460 --> 07:49.634
- Are you okay?
- <i>I just think I need to see someone.</i>

08:03.599 --> 08:06.917
I was walking around
and it started to rain.

08:07.304 --> 08:11.741
And... then I couldn't think
what it was that I needed.

08:12.370 --> 08:14.228
And then I remembered.

08:14.578 --> 08:16.931
But it's gone again.

08:36.599 --> 08:39.587
- Well, how's your week been?
- Special.

08:39.688 --> 08:41.655
- Oh, yeah.
- Very special.

08:41.755 --> 08:44.238
Do you want to tell me about it?

08:45.474 --> 08:49.179
I have these... intense feelings.

08:49.529 --> 08:52.864
- Do you want to talk to me about them?
- No, I don't want to talk about them.

09:00.089 --> 09:01.845
Sorry?

09:01.945 --> 09:04.441
I didn't say anything.

09:04.541 --> 09:06.597
You didn't?

09:06.697 --> 09:10.336
It's not like that,
it's... it's... It's more...

09:10.436 --> 09:12.718
It's more...

09:14.470 --> 09:17.674
Oh, God. No.

09:17.774 --> 09:19.543
- No?
- No.

09:19.743 --> 09:22.846
I sort of was going up
and down all the time,

09:22.946 --> 09:26.080
fluctuating with moods and...

09:26.180 --> 09:29.120
anxiety and depression, so in general...

09:29.220 --> 09:33.366
Just being overwhelmed like a tidal wave
had come over me,

09:33.466 --> 09:38.508
with so much new things
that took me to a dark place.

09:42.232 --> 09:46.321
I was exhausted, confused
and angry, and I had...

09:48.739 --> 09:51.295
I was exhausted...

09:58.764 --> 10:00.599
Dude.

10:03.703 --> 10:06.407
I'm sorry. I lost my train of thought.

10:07.457 --> 10:10.293
Train fucking derailed more like it.
Toot toot, Trav!

10:10.393 --> 10:12.629
Doctor. Okay, Dean?

10:12.729 --> 10:15.999
In this room, I'm doctor.

10:16.099 --> 10:18.137
I've got a question.

10:18.685 --> 10:21.929
Why are you doing this, man? Trav? Doc?

10:22.029 --> 10:23.540
Doing what?

10:23.640 --> 10:27.724
Nah, nah, come on, I'm asking. Serious.

10:28.879 --> 10:30.947
You're smart.

10:31.047 --> 10:34.324
You scrub up alright.
You could do what you want.

10:36.886 --> 10:38.989
Well, I don't want to do anything else.

10:39.389 --> 10:41.868
Helping make you feel good?

10:43.259 --> 10:45.825
Satisfied patients.

10:47.796 --> 10:51.568
- Let's talk about you, hey, Dean?
- No, no, let's talk about you.

10:52.068 --> 10:56.633
'Cause, I've heard something.
People have been talking, mate.

10:57.639 --> 11:03.367
Last week we were... we were
talking about you at the party...

11:04.030 --> 11:06.266
Not flash, brother.

11:06.366 --> 11:10.059
Doesn't inspire confidence
in the clientele, does it?

11:12.254 --> 11:14.891
Okay, Dean, well, we'll start
working when you're ready.

11:14.991 --> 11:17.027
One of your favorites.

11:17.127 --> 11:19.272
That's what I heard.

11:19.372 --> 11:21.390
That's cool.

11:21.490 --> 11:24.334
- She was mine too.
- Shut the fuck up, hey, Dean?

11:24.434 --> 11:28.638
Thought it was a bit harsh. Not exactly,
"Thank you, Doctor Travis", was it?

11:28.738 --> 11:32.077
No, Rachel...

11:37.880 --> 11:42.479
No, no, no, no, no! No!

11:54.263 --> 11:55.873
Dean is one of those patients

11:55.973 --> 11:59.136
- that can get under your skin.
- We both know it's not about him.

11:59.536 --> 12:01.504
Alright, then.

12:01.604 --> 12:03.940
Perhaps we should start by discussing
how you're coping...

12:04.040 --> 12:06.593
Was there something specific...

12:06.693 --> 12:09.326
you wanted to talk to me about?

12:11.280 --> 12:13.171
We think it would be best
for everyone if you...

12:13.271 --> 12:17.602
We? Oh, I'm sorry, I didn't realize
that there was somebody else here.

12:19.588 --> 12:22.025
Take a couple of weeks and think about...

12:22.125 --> 12:24.495
A couple of weeks.

12:24.795 --> 12:26.997
You firing me?

12:27.497 --> 12:30.817
- No, I'm not firing anyone!
- Just tell me. I can take it.

12:30.917 --> 12:34.613
I'm saying, take two or three weeks.

12:36.488 --> 12:39.686
What... Oh, Jesus, Trav!

12:48.150 --> 12:50.520
I tried to protect you.

12:50.620 --> 12:52.224
Right?

12:56.658 --> 12:58.613
Doctor?

13:09.538 --> 13:12.112
Hi, there, would you like a brochure?

13:13.275 --> 13:15.989
Excuse me, would you like
something to read?

13:16.778 --> 13:19.639
Would you like to ask a question with me?

13:21.717 --> 13:24.769
Ma'am, would you like
to ask a question with me?

13:26.822 --> 13:29.139
How about you, sir?

13:30.893 --> 13:32.719
Sir?

13:34.129 --> 13:35.937
What?

13:36.732 --> 13:38.665
Do you ever find yourself alone,

13:38.765 --> 13:42.450
or abandoned or in pain,
you could come and speak to us.

13:43.906 --> 13:46.491
There's a meeting tonight
if you wanted to come.

13:47.877 --> 13:50.253
I'm busy tonight.

13:50.713 --> 13:52.348
That's a shame.

14:15.300 --> 14:20.391
<i>Hey. It doesn't have to be now,
but pick up once.</i>

14:23.945 --> 14:26.896
<i>Okay, I'm going to keep trying you.</i>

14:30.119 --> 14:32.317
<i>I was discharged today.</i>

14:33.823 --> 14:35.851
I know.

14:36.226 --> 14:40.731
My dad came and collected me
from the hospital... took me home.

14:41.631 --> 14:44.667
They redecorated my old bedroom.

14:44.767 --> 14:49.046
Put all my old trophies up on the shelf.
Like a shrine.

14:51.056 --> 14:52.909
Violin.

14:53.460 --> 14:56.196
I played violin.

14:56.496 --> 14:57.724
Played?

14:58.124 --> 15:00.417
Why'd you stop?

15:00.517 --> 15:04.321
I wanted to see if I could be someone
other than a girl who plays the violin.

15:04.421 --> 15:05.956
Right.

15:06.056 --> 15:09.705
- And can you?
- I don't know.

15:14.063 --> 15:16.415
What time is it?

15:18.266 --> 15:19.956
About three.

15:20.904 --> 15:23.636
I shouldn't be here, should I?

15:24.757 --> 15:26.697
No.

15:31.913 --> 15:34.817
I think I just needed someone to...
you know?

15:34.917 --> 15:36.834
Yeah. Of course.

15:39.455 --> 15:42.775
It must get lonely having to listen
to everyone's crap all the time.

15:42.875 --> 15:47.119
Actually it's a nice break
from all the crap inside my own head.

15:56.672 --> 16:00.454
I don't think that...
that's such a good idea.

16:34.710 --> 16:36.014
Hi, I'm Tom. What's your name?

16:36.114 --> 16:38.161
- Hey. I'm Travis.
- Good to meet you, Travis.

16:38.261 --> 16:41.598
- Just through here?
- Yeah. Just round to your right.

16:56.199 --> 16:59.971
<i>I've served.
I've done a tour of duty of Iraq.</i>

17:01.470 --> 17:03.546
<i>And I've seen the terror first hand.</i>

17:06.708 --> 17:09.709
<i>I saw it for what it was
and I saw what caused it.</i>

17:09.809 --> 17:11.337
<i>In this time of danger...</i>

17:12.448 --> 17:16.031
<i>All these people burning up
with their own personal pain...</i>

17:18.753 --> 17:21.637
<i>And then they inflicted it
upon their world.</i>

17:26.328 --> 17:31.538
<i>But all that time, I couldn't stop thinking
that the hatred that kills hearts</i>

17:31.638 --> 17:33.419
<i>and kills each other...</i>

17:33.519 --> 17:36.170
<i>it all really comes from within.</i>

17:42.027 --> 17:46.316
<i>The biggest lie that they told after 9/11
was that the enemy is out there.</i>

17:46.416 --> 17:50.921
<i>You know, somewhere in a desert,
in a cave, waiting to strike.</i>

17:51.471 --> 17:53.647
<i>But the darkest
and most frightening enemy...</i>

17:54.057 --> 17:57.050
<i>is the enemy
who poisons himself from within</i>

17:57.150 --> 18:00.461
<i>because he can't see the terror
inside his own heart.</i>

18:05.601 --> 18:06.929
Okay, thanks everyone.

18:07.029 --> 18:10.642
Now you've seen that, it's time
for the important part of tonight.

18:11.191 --> 18:16.419
Marcus has committed to say something,
so let's give him our full support.

18:25.220 --> 18:27.847
You alright?

18:29.124 --> 18:32.102
Before I came here, I was an addict.

18:32.862 --> 18:35.232
Before I got here...

18:35.882 --> 18:39.119
everyone blamed me for being in my pain.

18:39.399 --> 18:44.297
It was when I got off of it, that's
when I realized how... how bad...

18:45.974 --> 18:48.278
- Look, you have to do this.
- I know...

18:48.378 --> 18:50.746
- Okay?
- I know.

18:52.013 --> 18:54.216
I know!

18:56.752 --> 19:00.870
I know I've fucked up my chances before,
but I won't do it again.

19:00.970 --> 19:03.476
You've shown me so much...

19:04.668 --> 19:07.197
about the injuries
that have been given to me.

19:07.297 --> 19:11.311
And why I've been in so much pain
and how it caused me to be an addict.

19:11.768 --> 19:15.082
And I know that with your help,
and with Father's help,

19:15.182 --> 19:18.641
and with Grace's help,
that I can get there.

19:18.741 --> 19:20.924
Okay. Tell them.

19:21.960 --> 19:24.497
I want to let go of my life.

19:24.597 --> 19:26.916
I want to join you on the farm.

19:27.016 --> 19:29.519
It's so beautiful there and...

19:29.619 --> 19:34.558
I promise... that if you let me,
I will join your family.

19:35.958 --> 19:39.435
And I will protect you
like you've protected me.

19:40.162 --> 19:42.999
And I will light the light
of my consciousness.

19:43.099 --> 19:45.526
I will light my light.

20:01.783 --> 20:06.321
This is a photo of me, and my mum
and my stepdad Glen.

20:08.023 --> 20:11.500
It's the only thing I have of my old life.

20:27.843 --> 20:30.127
It burns!

20:37.452 --> 20:42.105
- That's all you had to do.
- Thank you. Thank you.

20:48.230 --> 20:50.516
Something wrong, Travis?

20:50.917 --> 20:52.950
Not with me.

20:54.336 --> 20:57.373
You're the one making
the poor kid stand up here and...

20:57.473 --> 21:02.125
talk about some pretty difficult stuff
in front of a bunch of homeless people.

21:02.225 --> 21:04.227
No offense.

21:04.327 --> 21:06.215
- Is that what you see happening?
- Yeah, it is.

21:06.315 --> 21:08.681
'Cause, I see Marcus showing
a lot of courage and saying

21:08.781 --> 21:12.103
who he really wants to be and now
he's got somewhere where he belongs.

21:14.122 --> 21:16.567
You should be ashamed of yourself.

21:22.764 --> 21:24.600
Travis?

21:25.400 --> 21:27.303
Travis.

21:27.603 --> 21:31.388
- What?
- Don't stay away if you're in pain.

21:32.692 --> 21:34.439
Thanks.

21:57.182 --> 21:59.402
Come on. Do it.

21:59.802 --> 22:03.373
Do it. Just a little bit.
Just a little bit. Just a little bit.

22:03.473 --> 22:07.505
Not for them. Not for me. Just for you.

22:07.605 --> 22:10.345
Just for you. Come on, now.
Please, come on, please...

22:10.445 --> 22:14.175
- Okay, okay, okay.
- Thank you. Thank you.

22:14.916 --> 22:18.521
- But you have to go inside.
- Okay. Yes. Inside.

22:18.621 --> 22:20.356
Just... here?

22:20.456 --> 22:23.159
- Shut the door. Shut the door.
- Shut the door? Door is shutting.

22:23.259 --> 22:25.775
- Thank you.
- No worries.

23:32.862 --> 23:34.945
Five...

23:38.967 --> 23:42.183
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Hello, it's me.

23:43.405 --> 23:46.576
- It's Travis.
- <i>Travis, it's really late.</i>

23:46.676 --> 23:49.412
- Travis.
- <i>Okay.</i>

23:50.012 --> 23:53.783
Don't stay away if you're in pain...

23:53.883 --> 23:56.271
that's what she said.

23:56.486 --> 23:58.834
<i>What's happened, Travis?</i>

24:01.791 --> 24:06.128
- Pills, mostly.
- <i>Tell me, how many have you had?</i>

24:06.228 --> 24:08.531
Probably around forty.

24:08.631 --> 24:10.533
<i>Forty?</i>

24:10.633 --> 24:13.942
Maybe forty-seven.

24:15.870 --> 24:18.174
<i>Travis, where are you?</i>

24:18.274 --> 24:22.312
- <i>Tell me where you are.</i>
- I'm in my apartment.

24:23.112 --> 24:24.914
Where are you?

24:25.014 --> 24:28.150
- <i>What's your address?</i>
- Four seven three...

24:28.250 --> 24:29.952
- Four seven three king.
- <i>Can you hear me?</i>

24:30.052 --> 24:36.262
- Just around the corner from the church.
- Travis? We're coming. Just stay awake!

25:06.921 --> 25:11.085
There you go... that's it, just a sip...

25:11.185 --> 25:15.292
One sip... that's it... that's it.

25:33.548 --> 25:36.608
How do you feel?

25:37.719 --> 25:41.265
It doesn't matter.

26:49.624 --> 26:51.474
Hello.

26:56.264 --> 26:58.272
Who are you?

26:59.300 --> 27:00.970
Where am I?

27:01.070 --> 27:03.488
Please don't. Where are you going?

27:15.884 --> 27:17.968
Hello?

27:18.920 --> 27:20.801
Hello?

27:29.597 --> 27:33.318
- I've got something for you to drink, mate.
- I don't want to drink it.

27:33.418 --> 27:35.661
- You've got to. You've gotta drink it.
- I don't want to fucking drink it.

27:35.761 --> 27:37.973
You stay the fuck away from me.
I don't want to fucking drink it.

27:38.073 --> 27:41.410
Listen to me you fucking assholes,
just stay the fuck away from me, okay?

27:41.510 --> 27:45.674
Stay the fuck away from me!
I don't want to drink it!

27:45.981 --> 27:50.286
Tom, what are you doing?
What's he doing? I don't want to drink it.

27:50.386 --> 27:52.755
Please, just leave me alone,
I just want to get out of here.

27:52.855 --> 27:56.418
I just want to get out of here!
You fucking prick!

27:56.518 --> 27:59.762
Oh, fuck! What are you doing!

27:59.862 --> 28:02.932
You motherfuckers!

28:03.032 --> 28:05.652
Why are you doing this?

28:06.051 --> 28:07.921
What the fuck are you doing!

28:10.739 --> 28:13.044
I don't want it!

28:13.847 --> 28:15.932
I don't want...

28:25.520 --> 28:29.988
I don't want to...
I don't want to drink it.

28:30.625 --> 28:33.442
I don't want to drink it.

28:33.542 --> 28:36.117
You motherfuckers.

28:36.217 --> 28:39.167
I don't want to drink it.

28:39.667 --> 28:42.805
I don't want to drink it.

28:43.355 --> 28:46.171
I don't want to drink it.

30:26.207 --> 30:28.117
Thank you.

30:35.867 --> 30:38.574
Your body's judging you
for your addiction.

31:16.458 --> 31:19.117
When you're a whole person
you can have a whole meal.

31:21.195 --> 31:22.765
Can't wait.

31:22.965 --> 31:25.482
That's just how it works.

32:55.723 --> 32:58.045
What are you looking for?

33:02.263 --> 33:04.334
Painkillers.

33:06.167 --> 33:08.070
Oxycozin.

33:08.370 --> 33:10.560
Cirtrulline. Diazepam.

33:11.673 --> 33:14.476
Vodka. Gin.

33:14.726 --> 33:17.662
You don't have a bottle of gin, do you?

33:18.780 --> 33:20.649
We don't have any of that here.

33:20.749 --> 33:24.767
Of course you don't,
because that would be fun.

33:50.344 --> 33:52.795
Why do you do them?

33:54.315 --> 33:55.685
Do what?

33:56.335 --> 33:58.350
The pills.

34:00.254 --> 34:03.192
