- What are you doing?

44:18.540 --> 44:22.586
What are you gonna do about it?
What are you fucking afraid of?

44:29.416 --> 44:32.251
What are you gonna fucking do about it?

44:32.653 --> 44:35.845
Come on, come on.

44:45.078 --> 44:49.103
There you go! Now is there anything
you want to say to me?

44:49.203 --> 44:52.921
- Stay the fuck way from me!
- Yes!

45:00.981 --> 45:03.218
Come on, Trav, wait up, mate.

45:03.318 --> 45:05.025
I don't want your fucking help, okay?

45:05.125 --> 45:08.404
Okay. You're free to go.
Take the old merc if you like,

45:08.504 --> 45:10.825
it's nothing flash but it'll get you
where you need to go.

45:10.925 --> 45:14.014
Grab the keys will you please, Tom?
There's a map in the glovebox,

45:14.114 --> 45:17.399
just let us know where you leave the car
when you get to town, okay, Travis?

45:17.799 --> 45:20.221
- Travis!
- What?

45:21.069 --> 45:24.978
- The cars are this way, mate.
- Fucking shit!

45:32.031 --> 45:35.387
- Fuck!
- Just give it a bit more choke.

46:36.927 --> 46:38.876
Wait here.

46:56.730 --> 46:59.666
Life crisis is spirit crisis, Trav.

47:00.401 --> 47:02.337
Your doctors...

47:02.437 --> 47:06.772
kept you away from that knowing
because they didn't want you looking in.

47:07.108 --> 47:10.960
You're still right in the guts
of your addiction, mate.

47:30.931 --> 47:33.847
I don't know who I am anymore.

47:35.119 --> 47:37.738
I don't know how to live.

47:37.838 --> 47:40.541
That's why Tom brought you here.

47:40.641 --> 47:44.658
Because right now there's nothing
holding you together.

47:45.379 --> 47:48.216
But if you can feel your pain,

47:48.316 --> 47:52.146
then you can feel your real self. Yeah?

47:55.222 --> 47:57.058
Ask me.

47:57.158 --> 47:59.808
- Ask you what?
- You know.

48:04.599 --> 48:07.246
- Help me.
- Mean it.

48:08.969 --> 48:11.068
- Help me.
- Mean it.

48:12.239 --> 48:14.525
Help me.

48:16.209 --> 48:18.429
Help me.

48:24.301 --> 48:26.522
Help me.

48:31.858 --> 48:33.941
Like this?

48:34.427 --> 48:36.597
Like this?

48:36.697 --> 48:38.766
Is this the game?

48:38.866 --> 48:42.470
- Is this the game? Hit the bag.
- There's the anger.

48:42.570 --> 48:45.793
- The anger? Fuck off!
- Chickenshit.

48:45.893 --> 48:49.110
I'm a chickenshit, am I?
I'm a chickenshit.

48:49.210 --> 48:52.831
Chickenshit, am I? Is that...
how's that for fucking chickenshit?

48:53.781 --> 48:55.849
Like that?

48:55.949 --> 48:58.066
Get it!

49:01.122 --> 49:03.952
Violin's your favorite isn't it, Trav?

49:10.664 --> 49:12.543
Is this what you want?

49:16.603 --> 49:18.352
Okay.

49:27.280 --> 49:28.876
Come on.

49:32.552 --> 49:34.569
Come on.

49:36.690 --> 49:38.392
Come on.

49:38.492 --> 49:40.628
- Come on, mate.
- Come on, mate.

49:40.728 --> 49:43.598
There's the anger, come on.
Kill the bag, Travis. Kill the bag.

49:43.698 --> 49:45.600
- Harder.
- Let it out mate, let it out.

49:45.700 --> 49:48.269
Travis, let yourself go, mate! Come on!

49:48.369 --> 49:52.337
- Come on, give it.
- Harder. Harder. Harder...

50:29.075 --> 50:30.561
Die!

50:46.126 --> 50:48.600
Who are you angry with?

51:02.709 --> 51:05.060
Who are you angry with?

51:07.691 --> 51:10.248
Who are you angry with?

51:19.943 --> 51:22.244
Who are you angry with?

51:29.536 --> 51:31.252
Hey.

51:32.605 --> 51:35.290
- Hey.
- What are you taking?

51:39.162 --> 51:43.922
Just things are... starting to get
on top of me a little bit here and...

51:44.652 --> 51:47.772
and it feels really heavy.
I come home and it feels really heavy

51:47.872 --> 51:51.926
and I just... I don't know
where to go and it just...

51:52.026 --> 51:55.297
It's all just fucking stacking
on top of each other, you know?

51:56.130 --> 51:57.912
Okay.

52:02.769 --> 52:04.610
Travis.

52:05.310 --> 52:08.636
- What?
- I just want to help you, Trav.

52:08.736 --> 52:11.879
- You just want to help me?
- Yeah.

52:11.979 --> 52:15.629
You... want to help me?

52:20.854 --> 52:22.707
Come on.

52:24.591 --> 52:26.598
Oh, my...

52:28.061 --> 52:31.867
Yeah, laugh, laugh,
you can't fucking talk, though.

52:34.367 --> 52:37.009
No, no, no. No. What the...

52:39.389 --> 52:41.632
Open the door!

52:42.942 --> 52:46.447
I know I'm fucked up
but at least I can feel!

52:46.847 --> 52:51.454
You're such a kid. You're such a kid
and you're scared, Travis!

52:51.714 --> 52:54.822
Fuck! Travis just look at me!

53:00.193 --> 53:02.539
Talk to me!

53:06.065 --> 53:08.002
You're fucked.

53:08.102 --> 53:10.782
Completely fucked.

53:15.809 --> 53:17.993
Who do you want to talk to?

53:19.746 --> 53:21.982
You're me.

53:22.082 --> 53:24.766
What do you want to say to yourself?

53:30.523 --> 53:33.398
For as long as I can remember...

53:34.762 --> 53:36.572
I've hated you.

53:39.033 --> 53:41.669
You've always had a special way of...

53:41.769 --> 53:44.285
fucking everything up.

53:45.339 --> 53:48.576
<i>Travis, it's me, again.</i>

53:49.250 --> 53:52.747
<i>You don't have to pick up.
I know you're listening, though.</i>

53:52.847 --> 53:54.849
<i>I hope you're listening.</i>

53:54.949 --> 53:56.129
Tell me.

53:57.017 --> 53:59.453
You were always pretending.

53:59.553 --> 54:02.172
You're a pretender.

54:02.272 --> 54:04.542
<i>Oh, God.</i>

54:04.642 --> 54:06.977
<i>I knew you were a frightened child.</i>

54:07.077 --> 54:09.430
<i>I knew it when I first met you.</i>

54:09.530 --> 54:11.899
<i>It was okay, 'cause I thought that...</i>

54:11.999 --> 54:14.468
<i>It doesn't matter what I thought now,</i>

54:14.568 --> 54:16.767
<i>really, does it?</i>

54:18.705 --> 54:21.552
<i>It's so beautiful up here.</i>

54:22.943 --> 54:25.660
<i>It's like the top of the world.</i>

54:28.882 --> 54:31.399
<i>I can see everything.</i>

55:08.956 --> 55:12.092
I've just been trying to run away.

55:12.192 --> 55:16.317
I've just been running
and running and running.

55:17.497 --> 55:21.619
- Look at me.
- I don't want to look at you.

55:21.719 --> 55:25.923
I'm so sick of looking at you.

55:26.373 --> 55:30.528
I just... you make me sick.

55:31.545 --> 55:36.102
And now somebody's dead because of you.

55:36.383 --> 55:39.652
Because of what you did.

55:42.255 --> 55:44.472
So what now?

55:46.292 --> 55:50.690
I just... I just want to get rid of you.

55:50.790 --> 55:54.335
I just... I don't want to be
filled with that hatred,

55:54.435 --> 55:57.189
all the time.

56:00.089 --> 56:02.560
And when I'm gone...

56:02.960 --> 56:05.009
what's left?

56:05.828 --> 56:08.245
I don't know.

56:12.569 --> 56:14.785
Just nothing.

56:15.572 --> 56:17.837
Just nothing.

56:20.710 --> 56:22.535
Good.

56:38.728 --> 56:40.577
Thank you.

56:41.297 --> 56:44.394
- Thank you.
- Welcome, brother.

56:44.635 --> 56:46.974
- Thank you.
- Welcome, Travis.

56:47.074 --> 56:50.221
- We love you, Travis.
- Welcome, Travis.

56:54.711 --> 56:56.806
Thank you.

56:57.960 --> 56:59.796
Thank you.

56:59.896 --> 57:02.093
Thank you.

57:14.480 --> 57:16.289
Okay.

57:18.000 --> 57:20.538
I'm really glad you're healing.

57:20.638 --> 57:22.519
Me too.

57:23.072 --> 57:25.809
It's important for who you can be.

57:25.909 --> 57:27.746
Yeah.

57:30.079 --> 57:32.515
And who you can be with.

58:19.061 --> 58:21.463
To be a soldier of peace.

58:22.199 --> 58:24.715
To stand by Jay's side.

58:25.935 --> 58:28.319
To live in love.

58:29.055 --> 58:30.895
This is the purpose for my life.

58:32.441 --> 58:35.056
To find the joy in everything.

58:35.356 --> 58:37.514
Even in pain.

58:37.614 --> 58:39.885
That is the purpose of my life.

58:41.585 --> 58:43.421
To touch people with music.

58:43.621 --> 58:47.298
To show them there's meaning
and take them out of their pain.

58:48.925 --> 58:50.815
To share myself.

58:51.761 --> 58:54.164
And only this.

58:54.264 --> 58:56.348
This is the purpose of my life.

58:59.302 --> 59:03.381
To forgive those who tarnished me.

59:03.941 --> 59:05.648
To forgive myself.

59:07.161 --> 59:10.483
This is the purpose my soul
has chosen for my life.

59:12.415 --> 59:15.986
I think that I always wanted
to heal people.

59:16.787 --> 59:20.071
And somewhere along the way,
I forgot that.

59:21.024 --> 59:25.388
But, yeah, I think...
that's the purpose of my life.

59:35.905 --> 59:39.076
- How's it look?
- Trust me.

59:39.976 --> 59:43.523
- It looks good.
- Okay.

01:01:10.733 --> 01:01:14.171
You need to be exposed to what he did
to you, and how you feel about it.

01:01:14.271 --> 01:01:16.476
Do you understand?

01:01:18.107 --> 01:01:20.539
You have to feel your pain.

01:01:21.244 --> 01:01:23.547
That's the grief of letting go.

01:01:23.647 --> 01:01:26.233
And then it won't affect you anymore.

01:01:39.395 --> 01:01:44.094
Now you're connected to your pain,
you can look out from yourself.

01:01:44.194 --> 01:01:48.776
And now you can be with that special someone
whose soul feels the same as yours.

01:01:48.876 --> 01:01:51.088
Thank you, Jay.

01:03:40.717 --> 01:03:42.184
Hey.

01:03:42.284 --> 01:03:44.034
Hey.

01:03:45.788 --> 01:03:48.826
- How you doing?
- Yeah.

01:03:49.526 --> 01:03:52.896
You learn so much, right?

01:03:52.996 --> 01:03:56.633
I mean, I'm only starting to see
how far away from myself I was.

01:03:56.733 --> 01:03:59.076
You've been working really hard too.

01:03:59.176 --> 01:04:01.972
I think we're at that point
where we're gonna start

01:04:02.072 --> 01:04:04.678
breaking away from ourselves.

01:04:05.709 --> 01:04:08.412
- So you're feeling like you...
- it's like a calling, isn't it?

01:04:08.512 --> 01:04:11.671
Once you start
you just gotta keep on going.

01:04:12.716 --> 01:04:15.218
I've been so stupid.

01:04:15.318 --> 01:04:20.208
- I don't think that you're stupid...
